post_text:
Hello!

Moravia FFA wants to thank you for your generous support of our FFA program. We had an overwhelming amount of support for our small greenhouse, and couldn't appreciate you more.

One thing our program has never had to worry about is not being supported by our community. In a town the size of Moravia sometimes teachers worry that they may not have the support, or monetary support to give kids opportunities that create experiences for them. As a teacher in Moravia, I can say that I have never worried about that.

We thank you so much for all your wonderful comments and support during these challenging times.

With that being said, we only have one more sale left. From now, until Tuesday at noon all plants in the greenhouse will be half off. Due to the heat and nature of things, some of the plants are less healthy, and of course variety has went down. However, there are still a few plants left that may be of interest.

Thanks again Moravia, you are truly second to none.

post_text:
Right now our chapter should be sitting in Hilton, during the Iowa State FFA Convention, watching our 2019-20 President walk across the stage to receive her Iowa Degree.

Laney Hoffman has worked tirelessly to receive her award. She has worked a total of 3 SAE projects, competed in multiple FFA events, and held two separate offices within the chapter.

The Moravia FFA chapter is proud to have her as our leader, and look forward to having her involved in the chapter next year as Vice President.

Congratulation Laney!

post_text:
Moravia FFA will be opening the greenhouse for the first sale of the year this Saturday from 9-12!

We are offering vegetables, and many popular annual flowers and grasses.

Prices will be the following:
- All 4 packs $2.50
- Individual Pots $1.50 a piece
- Hanging baskets - $15
- Succulents - $2.00 a piece

Due to the circumstances we will be selling the plants using a honor system technique. There will be a safe box in the greenhouse where money can be deposited.

The greenhouse will be unlocked from 9-12 every Saturday from April 25th through the end of May.

Thanks for the continued support of the Moravia FFA chapter. We hope that this provides you with some normalcy as we continue on this path.

For FFA members showing livestock (swine, dairy cattle, beef cattle, dairy goats, meat goats, rabbits, horses, etc.) at any county fair or state fair, you need to be YQCA certified!

Below are instructions on how to do this online:
- During the month of April (April 1 – April 30), YQCA will be offering a 25% discount on the web-based training, making them $9.
- Those wishing to take part in the flash sale will need to purchase $9 web-based training coupons from YQCA.
- Please log on and create an account: https://yqca.learngrow.io
- For step-by-step instruction please go into this google folder for details: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/18rQr32Ao8nELnfHTqM0x1_Hk0wnmeU5R

post_text:
The Moravia FFA chapter had a busy day! We had a media visit from our Iowa State secretary as well as our South Central District secretary. They interviewed students about their SAE's, student class project, and much more! Look for a video outlining what our program is all about here soon.

Our other exciting news is that our horticulture program harvested their first crop of lettuce from their class hydroponic systems. Later this year we hope to be able to donate the school, and food banks with fresh tomatoes, cucumbers, and lettuce!

post_text:
10 of Moravia FFA's members had the opportunity to attend the 2019 National FFA attention this past week. After traveling over 1,000 miles, and visiting 5 states, we have returned. They toured Fair Oaks Farm in Illinois, Louisville Slugger Factory and Churchill downs in Louisville, St. Louis Zoo, saw Brett Young in Concert and of course attended the convention in Indianapolis.

I think all members grew closer together, and learned a lot of leadership qualities that they can bring back to the chapter. Thanks to all who support our chapter so that we can attend these trips, as well as Stephanie Dowdy who took time to help chaperone.

post_text: We post a lot about what is going on in Moravia FFA, but very little about what is happening in the classroom! Currently in class students are creating their own hydroponic/aquaponic systems to be used in the greenhouse, hatching chickens for a future Moravia FFA Egg layer flock, dissecting fish to learn external and internal anatomy, restoring a John Deere MT tractor, learning about swine evaluation, and building a chicken coop for the chicks hatching! Never a dull day!

Never a dull day!

post_text:
The Moravia FFA chapter had a busy week of hands on learning! The Ag II class finished learning pork wholesale and retail cuts, and then earned a trip to the Moravia Locker. Here they were able to see the processing of a pig from start to finish. Thank you Moravia Locker!

The Introduction to Ag. class took a break from SAE development to ultra sound their goats. Each student was able to ultra sound. One is pregnant with triplets, while the other two were questionable, so we drew blood for exact results. Thanks to Garver Animal Health Center for letting Dr. Webb come down!

One is pregnant with triplets, while the other two were questionable, so we drew blood for exact results. Thanks to Garver Animal Health Center for letting Dr. Webb come down!

post_text: Moravia FFA Members participated at SC District FFA Convention on March 10, 2018. Members displayed their knowledge and learned how they can improve throughout the day. Greenhand Quiz Team received Silver, Treasurer's Book received Bronze, Chapter Website received Gold, Welding received Gold. Members in attendance also presented a Moravia FFA Jacket to Cassie Bond, Iowa FFA State VP-SC District, to be displayed at the FFA Booth in the Ag Building at Iowa State Fair, look for it this summer. Congratulations to Moravia FFA on a successful SC District Convention.
